Application Data can be Backed up

manifest_analysis.desc: This flag allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object does not have RELRO enabled. The entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) are writable. playstore_details.title: iPwR OTP Generator
playstore_details.description:
iPwR OTP Generator utility allows DXC Bionix iPwR desktop application users to dynamically generate one-time passcode (OTP) key every 60 seconds from your Phone, associated to a unique CredentialID linked to your email, providing a more reliable level of user authentication than reusable passwords, to perform the tasks need on the desktop application such as password reset and unlock your local computer account.

Note: To use this application, you first need to login with the appropriate credentials. These credentials should be provided to you by your system administrator, if not, proceed with the Sign Up for a New Account.

Sign Up: After installing this application, you will need to Sign Up for a New Account. Once you complete the sign-up process, you will be provided with the credentials needed to Login to start using the functionality with the convenience, simplicity and ease of use of one-time passcode on the DXC Bionix iPwR desktop application.
